The previous 'Find' command can only support multiple 'Name' keywords.

We want Socius to support all properties (e.g. 'Social', 'Tutorial Group', etc)

This commit implements an updated 'Find' command that supports multiple keywords of all properties. The format follows 'Add' and 'Edit'. A 'MultipleParsers' class was implemented to easily track how many of what Predicates are in use in a 'Find' command.

This commit introduces new Test Cases for 'FindCommand' and the various Parsers.
This commit also fixed minor documentation bugs from the previous 'FindCommand' commit.

commitResults.messageTitle: Patch emptyString bug for Find and DeleteMultiple
commitResults.messageBody:
"find n/ n/Test" will list all persons, because the first search term is "" and emptyString is found in all string.

This bug fix fix this specific problem by preventing users from typing empty string

Previously, entries with the same Name is treated as the same person.

According to @kwokieee, this is a bug as it prevents me from adding friends whose full name I may not know (e.g multiple 'John's).

To solve this, I have changed the method which check if 2 persons are the same to follow the 'equals' method. This means 2 persons are duplicate, only if all details of them are the same, which sounds like a valid reason to give.

Phone Number:
There is no upper limit of the length of phone number.

According to @luminousleek, long phone number should not be accepted. [Valid point]

I have tweaked the phone number to accept up to 15 numbers. The longest phone number in the world is 15 numbers (India's phone number with country code).

All commands which involves the parsing of Index will return an Invalid Command Format when a Non-Zero Integer cannot be parsed.

According to @xianlinc, the correct error should be 'The person index provided is invalid', no matter how large the input number. [Valid point]

I've added a check, such that all string that
1. Contains just numbers AND
2. Not the integer range (i.e between -2 billion to 2 billion) AND
3. Is a positive number (any length), but must not be all 0s...
will return Integer.MAX_INT.
This assumes that the users will not have 2.147 billion friends in Socius, which should be a reasonable assumption to make (Consider the size of json file and time taken to import!!)
